2026-05-20 | Prefix Common Array of Two Permutations

	Question
Return prefix common array C.
	Key Insight
As we move index by index:
		track visited numbers.
If a number appears in both arrays so far:
		it contributes to common count.
	Approach
1.	Create frequency/visited array  
2.	Process indices from 0 to n-1:
		add A[i]
		add B[i]
3.	If after insertion:
		a value becomes seen in both arrays:
				increase common count
4.	Store current count in answer.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> findThePrefixCommonArray(vector<int>& A,
                                         vector<int>& B) {
        int n = A.size();
        vector<int> freq(n + 1, 0);
        vector<int> ans(n);
        int common = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            freq[A[i]]++;
            if(freq[A[i]] == 2)
                common++;
            freq[B[i]]++;
            if(freq[B[i]] == 2)
                common++;
            ans[i] = common;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
A number becomes “common”
exactly when it has appeared:
		once in A prefix
		and once in B prefix  
So:
		frequency reaching 2
		means newly common element.
